  "base_commit": "389a084d5225cdf775cea6397cf8218e00169036",
  "pr_number": 14954,
  "issue_number": 14583,
  "issue_title": "Template files are not correctly autocorrected",
  "issue_body": "There is an issue where the template support feature does not work correctly with RuboCop's autocorrect feature, and I\u2019m not sure how to modify `lib/rubocop/runner.rb` to fix it, so could you help me?\n\nThe problem is as follows:\n\nFor example, suppose `example.erb` contains three `<% ... %>` blocks, and each of them has one offense.\n\n```erb\n<% ... %>\n<% ... %>\n<% ... %>\n```\n\nWhen running `rubocop --autocorrect example.erb`, RuboCop detects all three offenses and shows them as `[Corrected]` in the output, but in reality only the last reported offense is actually autocorrected in the file. Because of this problem, for example, with this template file, you would need to run `rubocop --autocorrect example.erb` a total of three times before all corrections are actually applied.\n\nInside `RuboCop::Runner`, what happens is that autocorrect is applied three times for `example.erb`. However, each of these is treated as if it were a different file. As a result, the `File.write` from the second autocorrect overwrites the changes from the first, and the `File.write` from the third overwrites the second, so only the last correction remains.\n\nThe reason this happens is that, to support templates, the existing implementation represents each embedded Ruby snippet in the same template file as a combination of file path + offset. `RuboCop::Runner` then treats these as different files.\n\nI believe this issue can be resolved if we can modify the code so that these snippets are recognized as the same file and autocorrections for the same file are properly grouped and applied.\n\nAlso, although this is unrelated to the autocorrect issue, it seems that the caching mechanism doesn\u2019t work properly for files analyzed using the template API. I haven\u2019t investigated this issue in detail yet, so I can\u2019t say anything definitive at this point.\n\n---\n\nrelevant links:\n\n- https://github.com/rubocop/rubocop/pull/10839\n- https://github.com/r7kamura/rubocop-slim/issues/12\n- https://github.com/r7kamura/rubocop-haml/issues/18",
  "merged_at": "2026-04-11T05:41:01Z",
